{"title_page": "Alfons Groenendijk", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2020}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name        = Alfons Groenendijk\n| image       = Alfons Groenendijk (2017).jpg\n| image_size  = 200\n| caption     = Groenendijk with [[ADO Den Haag]] in 2017\n| fullname    = Alfons Groenendijk\n| birth_date  = {{birth date and age|1964|5|17|df=yes}}\n| birth_place = [[Leiden]], Netherlands\n| height      =\n| currentclub =\n| position    = [[Midfielder]]\n| youthyears1 = 1972\u20131976 | youthclubs1   = LFC\n| youthyears2 = 1976\u20131982 | youthclubs2   = UVS\n| years1      = 1982\u20131987 | clubs1   = [[ADO Den Haag|FC Den Haag]] | caps1   = 119 | goals1   = 22\n| years2      = 1987\u20131991 | clubs2   = [[Roda JC Kerkrade|Roda JC]] | caps2 = 107 | goals2   = 21\n| years3      = 1991\u20131993 | clubs3   = [[AFC Ajax|Ajax]] | caps3   = 22 | goals3   = 1\n| years4      = 1993\u20131994 | clubs4   = [[Manchester City F.C.|Manchester City]] | caps4   = 9 | goals4   = 0\n| years5      = 1994\u20131998 | clubs5   = [[Sparta Rotterdam]] | caps5   = 105 | goals5   = 11\n| years6      = 1998\u20132001 | clubs6   = [[FC Utrecht|Utrecht]] | caps6   = 51 | goals6   = 7\n| totalcaps   = 413 | totalgoals = 62\n| manageryears1 = 2001\u20132003 | managerclubs1   = [[VV Katwijk]]\n| manageryears2 = 2005\u20132006 | managerclubs2   = [[Jong Ajax]] (assistant)\n| manageryears3 = 2006\u20132008 | managerclubs3   = [[AFC Ajax|Ajax]] (assistant)\n| manageryears4 = 2008\u20132009 | managerclubs4   = [[Willem II (football club)|Willem II]] (assistant)\n| manageryears5 = 2009\u20132010 | managerclubs5   = [[Willem II (football club)|Willem II]]\n| manageryears6 = 2010\u20132012 | managerclubs6   = [[FC Den Bosch|Den Bosch]]\n| manageryears7 = 2013\u20132014 | managerclubs7   = [[Jong Ajax]]\n| manageryears8 = 2014      | managerclubs8   = [[FC Universitatea Cluj|Universitatea Cluj]] (technical director)\n| manageryears9 = 2015\u20132016 | managerclubs9   = [[SBV Excelsior|Excelsior]]\n| manageryears10= 2017\u20132019 | managerclubs10  = [[ADO Den Haag]]\n}}\n'''Alfons Groenendijk''' ({{IPA-nl|\u02c8\u0251lf\u0254ns \u02c8xrun\u0259(n)d\u025bik}};<ref>In isolation, ''Groenendijk'' is pronounced {{IPA-nl|\u02c8\u0263run\u0259(n)d\u025bik|}}.</ref> born 17 May 1964) is a Dutch former professional [[Association football|footballer]] and current [[Manager (association football)|manager]].\n\n==Club career==\nDuring his career, Groenendijk played for [[ADO Den Haag]], [[Roda JC Kerkrade|Roda JC]], [[AFC Ajax|Ajax]], [[Manchester City F.C.|Manchester City]], [[Sparta Rotterdam]], and [[FC Utrecht|Utrecht]]. With Ajax, he won the [[1991\u201392 UEFA Cup]] and the [[1992\u201393 KNVB Cup]].\n\n==Managerial career==\nGroenendijk has been appointed assistant manager of [[Willem II (football club)|Willem II]] for the 2008\u201309 season. He was previously a manager of [[Jong Ajax]] and amateur side [[VV Katwijk]]. He became manager of Willem II in February 2009, succeeding [[Andries Jonker]] who became director of football for Willem II. On 19 February 2010, Willem II decided to sack Groenendijk.\n\n==Honours==\n'''Ajax'''\n*[[KNVB Cup]]: [[1992\u201393 KNVB Cup|1992\u201393]]\n*[[UEFA Europa League|UEFA Cup]]: [[1991\u201392 UEFA Cup|1991\u201392]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://www.beijen.net/frank/cvs/groenendijk-a.htm Alfons Groenendijk] at Beijen.net\n*{{Soccerbase}}\n\n{{Netherlands-footy-midfielder-stub}}\n\n{{Navboxes\n|title = Alfons Groenendijk managerial positions\n|list1 =\n{{Willem II managers}}\n{{FC Den Bosch managers}}\n{{Jong Ajax managers}}\n{{SBV Excelsior managers}}\n{{ADO Den Haag managers}}\n}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Groenendijk, Alfons}}\n[[Category:1964 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Expatriate footballers in England]]\n[[Category:Dutch expatriate footballers]]\n[[Category:Dutch footballers]]\n[[Category:Association football midfielders]]\n[[Category:Dutch football managers]]\n[[Category:Eredivisie players]]\n[[Category:Eerste Divisie players]]\n[[Category:Premier League players]]\n[[Category:ADO Den Haag players]]\n[[Category:Roda JC Kerkrade players]]\n[[Category:AFC Ajax players]]\n[[Category:Manchester City F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Sparta Rotterdam players]]\n[[Category:FC Utrecht players]]\n[[Category:Footballers from Leiden]]\n[[Category:AFC Ajax non-playing staff]]\n[[Category:Willem II (football club) managers]]\n[[Category:FC Den Bosch managers]]\n[[Category:Jong Ajax managers]]\n[[Category:SBV Excelsior managers]]\n[[Category:ADO Den Haag managers]]\n[[Category:UEFA Cup winning players]]\n[[Category:Eredivisie managers]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox football biography\n| name        = Alfons Groenendijk\n| image       = Alfons Groenendijk (2017).jpg\n| image_size  = 200\n| caption     = Groenendijk with [[ADO Den Haag]] in 2017\n| fullname    = Alfons Groenendijk\n| birth_date  = {{birth date and age|1964|5|17|df=yes}}\n| birth_place = [[Leiden]], Netherlands\n| height      =\n| currentclub =\n| position    = [[Midfielder]]\n| youthyears1 = 1972\u20131976 | youthclubs1   = LFC\n| youthyears2 = 1976\u20131982 | youthclubs2   = UVS\n| years1      = 1982\u20131987 | clubs1   = [[ADO Den Haag|FC Den Haag]] | caps1   = 119 | goals1   = 22\n| years2      = 1987\u20131991 | clubs2   = [[Roda JC Kerkrade|Roda JC]] | caps2 = 107 | goals2   = 21\n| years3      = 1991\u20131993 | clubs3   = [[AFC Ajax|Ajax]] | caps3   = 22 | goals3   = 1\n| years4      = 1993\u20131994 | clubs4   = [[Manchester City F.C.|Manchester City]] | caps4   = 9 | goals4   = 0\n| years5      = 1994\u20131998 | clubs5   = [[Sparta Rotterdam]] | caps5   = 105 | goals5   = 11\n| years6      = 1998\u20132001 | clubs6   = [[FC Utrecht|Utrecht]] | caps6   = 51 | goals6   = 7\n| totalcaps   = 413 | totalgoals = 62\n| manageryears1 = 2001\u20132003 | managerclubs1   = [[VV Katwijk]]\n| manageryears2 = 2005\u20132006 | managerclubs2   = [[Jong Ajax]] (assistant)\n| manageryears3 = 2006\u20132008 | managerclubs3   = [[AFC Ajax|Ajax]] (assistant)\n| manageryears4 = 2008\u20132009 | managerclubs4   = [[Willem II (football club)|Willem II]] (assistant)\n| manageryears5 = 2009\u20132010 | managerclubs5   = [[Willem II (football club)|Willem II]]\n| manageryears6 = 2010\u20132012 | managerclubs6   = [[FC Den Bosch|Den Bosch]]\n| manageryears7 = 2013\u20132014 | managerclubs7   = [[Jong Ajax]]\n| manageryears8 = 2014      | managerclubs8   = [[FC Universitatea Cluj|Universitatea Cluj]] (technical director)\n| manageryears9 = 2015\u20132016 | managerclubs9   = [[SBV Excelsior|Excelsior]]\n| manageryears10= 2017\u20132019 | managerclubs10  = [[ADO Den Haag]]\n}}\n'''Alfons Groenendijk''' ({{IPA-nl|\u02c8\u0251lf\u0254ns \u02c8xrun\u0259(n)d\u025bik}};<ref>In isolation, ''Groenendijk'' is pronounced {{IPA-nl|\u02c8\u0263run\u0259(n)d\u025bik|}}.</ref> born 17 May 1964) is a Dutch former professional [[Association football|footballer]] and current [[Manager (association football)|manager]].\n\n==Club career==\nDuring his career, Groenendijk played for [[ADO Den Haag]], [[Roda JC Kerkrade|Roda JC]], [[AFC Ajax|Ajax]], [[Manchester City F.C.|Manchester City]], [[Sparta Rotterdam]], and [[FC Utrecht|Utrecht]]. With Ajax, he won the [[1991\u201392 UEFA Cup]] and the [[1992\u201393 KNVB Cup]].\n\n==Managerial career==\nGroenendijk has been appointed assistant manager of [[Willem II (football club)|Willem II]] for the 2008\u201309 season. He was previously a manager of [[Jong Ajax]] and amateur side [[VV Katwijk]]. He became manager of Willem II in February 2009, succeeding [[Andries Jonker]] who became director of football for Willem II. On 19 February 2010, Willem II decided to sack Groenendijk.\n\n==Honours==\n'''Ajax'''\n*[[KNVB Cup]]: [[1992\u201393 KNVB Cup|1992\u201393]]\n*[[UEFA Europa League|UEFA Cup]]: [[1991\u201392 UEFA Cup|1991\u201392]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://www.beijen.net/frank/cvs/groenendijk