{"title_page": "Frederiksberg Municipality", "text_new": "{{distinguish|Frederiksborg County}}\n{{Infobox settlement\n| name                    = Frederiksberg Municipality\n| native_name             = Frederiksberg Kommune\n| other_name              = \n| settlement_type         = Municipalities of Denmark\n<!-- images, nickname, motto -->\n| image_skyline           = Frederiksberg kommune.jpg\n| image_caption           = \n| image_flag              = \n| image_shield            = \n| motto                   = \n| nickname                = \n| etymology               = \n<!-- location -->\n| subdivision_type        = Country\n| subdivision_name        = Denmark\n| subdivision_type1       = \n| subdivision_name1       = \n| subdivision_type2       = Region\n| subdivision_name2       = [[Capital Region of Denmark|Region Hovedstaden]]\n| subdivision_type3       = \n| subdivision_name3       = \n| subdivision_type4       = \n| subdivision_name4       = \n<!-- maps and coordinates -->\n| image_map               = Map DK Frederiksberg.PNG\n| map_caption             = \n| pushpin_map             = \n| pushpin_relief          = \n| pushpin_map_caption     =  \n| coordinates             = \n| coordinates_footnotes   = \n<!-- government type, leaders -->\n| leader_title1           = Mayor\n| leader_name1            = Simon Aggesen\n<!-- seat -->\n| seat                    = [[Frederiksberg]]\n| seat_type               = Seat\n<!-- established -->\n| established_title       = \n| established_date        = \n<!-- area -->\n| area_footnotes          = \n| area_total_km2          = 8.7\n| area_total_sq_mi        = \n| area_land_sq_mi         = \n| area_water_sq_mi        = \n<!-- elevation -->\n| elevation_footnotes     = \n| elevation_m             = \n| elevation_ft            = \n<!-- population -->\n| population_as_of        = 1 January 2019\n| population_footnotes    = \n| population_total        = 103960<ref>[http://www.statistikbanken.dk/FOLK1 FOLK1: Population 1 January] database from [[Statistics Denmark]] {{in lang|da}}</ref>\n| population_density_km2  = auto\n| population_density_sq_mi=\n| population_demonym      = \n<!-- time zone(s) -->\n| timezone1               = [[Central European Time|CET]]\n| utc_offset1             = 1\n| timezone1_DST           = [[Central European Summer Time|CEST]]\n| utc_offset1_DST         = 2\n<!-- postal codes, area code -->\n| postal_code_type        = \n| postal_code             = \n| area_code_type          =  \n| area_code               = \n| geocode                 = \n| iso_code                = \n<!-- website, footnotes -->\n| website                 = {{URL|http://www.frederiksberg.dk/OmKommunen/English.aspx}}\n| footnotes               = \n}}\n[[File:Kopenhagen-frederiksberg.PNG|225px|thumb|right|Locator map in [[Copenhagen]]]]\n[[File:Denmark Frederiksberg Palace.JPG|225px|thumb|right|[[Frederiksberg Palace]]]]\n'''Frederiksberg Kommune''' is a [[Municipalities of Denmark|municipality]] ([[Danish language|Danish]], ''[[Commune (subnational entity)|kommune]]'') on the island of [[Zealand (Denmark)|Zealand]] (''Sj\u00e6lland'') in [[Denmark]]. Part of [[Copenhagen]], it is surrounded by [[Copenhagen Municipality]]. The municipality, co-extensive with [[Frederiksberg|its seat]], covers a total area (land and water) of {{convert|8.71|km2|sqmi ha||abbr=in }} according to the Municipal Key Figures<ref>[www.noegletal.dk ''De Kommunale N\u00f8gletal'']</ref> and has a population of 103,960 (1 January 2019) making it the smallest municipality in Denmark area-wise, the fifth most populous, and the most densely populated. Its mayor is Simon Aggesen from the [[Conservative People's Party (Denmark)|Conservative People's Party]] (''Det Konservative Folkeparti'').\n\nThe city of [[Frederiksberg]] is the only town in the municipality, and is therefore the site of its municipal council.\n\nFrederiksberg is located as an [[enclave]] within the [[Copenhagen municipality|municipality of Copenhagen]], the national capital. The municipality was originally situated west of Copenhagen, but after a number of smaller municipalities were merged with Copenhagen in 1901, it became completely surrounded by Copenhagen.\n\nFrederiksberg was one of the three last Danish municipalities not belonging to a [[Counties of Denmark|County]]\u2014the others being [[Copenhagen]] and [[Bornholm]]. On 1 January 2007, the municipality lost its county privileges and became part of [[Region Hovedstaden]] (i.e. the ''Copenhagen Capital Region'').\n\nFrederiksberg municipality was not merged with other municipalities as the result of nationwide [[Municipalities of Denmark#Municipal Reform 2007|''Kommunalreformen'' (\"The Municipal Reform\" of 2007)]].\n\n==Main sights==\n* [[Frederiksberg Campus (University of Copenhagen)]]\n* [[Frederiksberg Gardens]]\n* [[Frederiksberg Hospital]]\n* [[Frederiksberg Palace]]\n* [[Frederiksberg Town Hall]]\n* [[Copenhagen Business School]]\n* [[Copenhagen Zoo]]\n* [[Royal Danish Military Academy]]\n* [[Church of the Deaf]]\n\n==Mayors==\n* [[Marius Godskesen]] (1919\u20131936)\n* [[Vilhelm Fischer]] (1936\u20131948)\n* [[Aksel M\u00f8ller]] (1948\u20131950, 1954\u20131958)\n* [[Arne St\u00e6hr Johansen]] (1950\u20131954, 1958\u20131978)\n* [[John Winther]] (1978\u20132000)\n* [[Mads Lebech]] (2001\u20132009)\n* [[J\u00f8rgen Glenth\u00f8j]] (2009\u20132019)\n* [[Simon Aggesen]] (2019-)\n\n==Twin towns==\n{{See also|List of twin towns and sister cities in Denmark}}\nFrederiksberg Municipality is [[Twin towns and sister cities|twinned]] with:<ref name=\"Frederiksberg\">{{cite web|url=http://www.frederiksberg.dk/PolitikOgDemokrati/PolitikkerOgStrategier/Samarbejde/InternationaleSamarbejder/Venskabsbyer.aspx |title=Frederiksberg Municipality - Twin Towns |publisher=[[copyright|\u00a9]]2007 -2009 [http://www.frederiksberg.dk/OmKommunen/English/AboutTheMunicipality.aspx Frederiksberg Municipality] |language=Danish |accessdate=2009-09-09 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110615162533/http://www.frederiksberg.dk/PolitikOgDemokrati/PolitikkerOgStrategier/Samarbejde/InternationaleSamarbejder/Venskabsbyer.aspx |archivedate=2011-06-15 }}</ref>\n*{{flagicon|EST}} [[Tartu]], [[Estonia]] <ref name=\"Frederiksberg\"/><ref name=\"Tartu\">{{cite web|url=http://tartu.ee/?lang_id=2&menu_id=11&page_id=1737|title=Co-operation with twin and partner cities|publisher=[[copyright|\u00a9]]2007 City of Tartu|accessdate=2009-01-04}}</ref>\n*{{flagicon|SWE}} [[Uppsala]], [[Uppsala County|Uppsala l\u00e4n]], [[Sweden]]<ref name=\"Frederiksberg\"/>\n*{{flagicon|NOR}} [[B\u00e6rum]], [[Norway]]<ref name=\"Frederiksberg\"/>\n*{{flagicon|FIN}} [[H\u00e4meenlinna]], [[Southern Finland|Etel\u00e4-Suomi]], [[Finland]]<ref name=\"Frederiksberg\"/>\n*{{flagicon|ISL}} [[Hafnarfj\u00f6r\u00f0ur]], [[Iceland]]<ref name=\"Frederiksberg\"/>\n*{{flagicon|LAT}} [[C\u0113sis]], [[Latvia]]<ref name=\"Frederiksberg\"/>\n\n==See also==\n* [[Frederiksberg station]]\n\n==Notes and references==\n<!--This article uses the Cite.php citation mechanism. If you would like more information on how to add references to this article, please see http://meta.wikimedia.org/wiki/Cite/Cite.php -->\n{{reflist}}\n* Municipal statistics: [https://web.archive.org/web/20070812152043/http://www2.netborger.dk/Kommunefakta/ NetBorger Kommunefakta], delivered from [http://www.kmd.dk/ KMD aka Kommunedata (Municipal Data)]\n* Municipal mergers and neighbors: [https://web.archive.org/web/20071011050224/http://kommune.eniro.dk/danmarkskort/ Eniro new municipalities map]\n*[http://www.statistikbanken.dk/statbank5a/default.asp?w=1280]\n\n==External links==\n{{commons category|Frederiksberg Kommune|Friedriksberg Municipality}}\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20051017033955/http://www.frederiksberg.dk/English.aspx Municipality's official website]\n\n{{Frederiksberg, Copenhagen}}\n{{Municipalities of Denmark}}\n{{Copenhagen}}\n{{Coord|55|40|40|N|12|32|0|E|display=title}}\n\n[[Category:Frederiksberg Municipality| ]]\n[[Category:Enclaves and exclaves]]\n[[Category:Copenhagen metropolitan area]]\n[[Category:Municipalities in the Capital Region of Denmark]]\n[[Category:Municipalities of Denmark]]\n", "text_old": "{{distinguish|Frederiksborg County}}\n{{Infobox settlement\n| name                    = Frederiksberg Municipality\n| native_name             = Frederiksberg Kommune\n| other_name              = \n| settlement_type         = Municipalities of Denmark\n<!-- images, nickname, motto -->\n| image_skyline           = Frederiksberg kommune.jpg\n| image_caption           = \n| image_flag              = \n| image_shield            = \n| motto                   = \n| nickname                = \n| etymology               = \n<!-- location -->\n| subdivision_type        = Country\n| subdivision_name        = Denmark\n| subdivision_type1       = \n| subdivision_name1       = \n| subdivision_type2       = Region\n| subdivision_name2       = [[Capital Region of Denmark|Region Hovedstaden]]\n| subdivision_type3       = \n| subdivision_name3       = \n| subdivision_type4       = \n| subdivision_name4       = \n<!-- maps and coordinates -->\n| image_map               = Map DK Frederiksberg.PNG\n| map_caption             = \n| pushpin_map             = \n| pushpin_relief          = \n| pushpin_map_caption     =  \n| coordinates             = \n| coordinates_footnotes   = \n<!-- government type, leaders -->\n| leader_title1           = Mayor\n| leader_name1            = Simon Aggesen\n<!-- seat -->\n| seat                    = [[Frederiksberg]]\n| seat_type               = Seat\n<!-- established -->\n| established_title       = \n| established_date        = \n<!-- area -->\n| area_footnotes          = \n| area_total_km2          = 8.7\n| area_total_sq_mi        = \n| area_land_sq_mi         = \n| area_water_sq_mi        = \n<!-- elevation -->\n| elevation_footnotes     = \n| elevation_m             = \n| elevation_ft            = \n<!-- population -->\n| pop